# Portfolio Core

Personal brand platform (Next.js 16+, React 19, TypeScript strict, Tailwind v4, shadcn/ui, Dracula/Alucard palette, Supabase, Vercel).

## Commands

```bash
yarn dev          # Local Supabase + Next.js (sequential)
yarn dev:next     # Next.js only
yarn db:start     # Start local Supabase
yarn db:reset     # Reset local DB (migrations + seed)
yarn build && yarn lint && yarn typecheck && yarn test
yarn sync:ai      # Mirror .claude/agents+skills <-> .cursor/agents+skills
```

Database setup: `docs/supabase.md`. AI workflow (Cursor): `docs/ai/cursor-workflow.md`.

## Conventions

- Server Components by default; `"use client"` only when needed.
- Design values via tokens only — no hardcoded colors, spacing, or font sizes.
- WCAG 2.1 AA minimum. No external state libraries.
- Prefer editing existing files. No comments unless the "why" is non-obvious.
- No premature abstractions. `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` and `admin.ts` are server-only.
- Next.js 16 uses `proxy.ts` instead of `middleware.ts`.

## Quality Gate (before merge)

1. Lighthouse Performance and Accessibility > 95.
2. Keyboard-navigable interactive elements with visible focus.
3. Contrast 4.5:1 text, 3:1 UI components.
4. Viewport 320px–2560px.
5. First Load JS < 100kB per route.

Full checklists: `.cursor/skills/quality-gate/`.
